Interface ResourceLoader

public interface ResourceLoader
Loader of individually named resource.

This is mimicking the method signatures of ClassLoader.

This is essentially a low-level service-provider-interface, not to be used directly.

Since:
2025-06-26
Author:
Morten Sabroe Mortensen

  • Method Details

    • getResource

      URL getResource(String name)
      Gets a reference to a resource.

      If multiple resources with the same name exists, then this is one of them. To get all resources with the same name, use getResources(String), resources(String) or getResourcesAsList(String).

      See ClassLoader.getResource(String).

      Parameters:
      name - Resource name.
      Returns:
      Reference to resource. This can be used to access the resource.

    • getResourceAsStream

      InputStream getResourceAsStream(String name)
      Gets access to resource content as an input-stream.

      If multiple resources with the same name exists, then this opens access to one of them. To get all resources with the same name, use getResources(String), resources(String) or getResourcesAsList(String), and use the reference URLs to open access.

      See ClassLoader.getResourceAsStream(String).

      Parameters:
      name - Resource name.
      Returns:
      Input-stream to resource content.

    • getResources

      Enumeration<URL> getResources(String name) throws IOException
      Gets references to all resources with the same name.

      See ClassLoader.getResources(String).

      If multiple resources are present, then it may be one file URL for classes and one file URL for resources.

      Parameters:
      name - Resource name.
      Returns:
      References to resources. These can be used to access the resources.
      Throws:
      IOException

    • resources

      Stream<URL> resources(String name)
      Gets references to all resources with the same name.

      See ClassLoader.resources(String).

      If multiple resources are present, then it may be one file URL for classes and one file URL for resources.

      Parameters:
      name - Resource name.
      Returns:
      References to resources. These can be used to access the resources.

    • getResourceAsChannel

      default ReadableByteChannel getResourceAsChannel(String name)
      Gets access to resource content as a readable byte-channel.

      If multiple resources with the same name exists, then this opens access to one of them. To get all resources with the same name, use getResources(String), resources(String) or getResourcesAsList(String), and use the reference URLs to open access.

      See ClassLoader.getResourceAsStream(String).

      Parameters:
      name - Resource name.
      Returns:
      Readable byte-channel to resource content.

      Returns:
      Indicates, if the resource exists.
